    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on the Medium model influence classification and the conservative nature of the single ASTM F1717 load condition, which represents worst-case clinical loading. All three primary QoIs satisfy both the <10% relative difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for predicting non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending performance in support of the regulatory submission.",
